Next, I need to find all fixed asset purchase transactions in the data. Looking through the transactions, I found:

So I have two fixed asset purchases totaling:

## Step 3: Identify depreciation
Now I need to find all depreciation transactions:

```
| Depreciation20240101001 | Depreciation | 2024-01-01 | 2024-01-01 | 45745.8 | 45745.8 |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |

```

So there are two depreciation entries totaling:
45,745.80 + 69,766.11 = 115,511.91

## Step 4: Calculate the net fixed assets value

Initial fixed assets value: 8,000,000.00
+ Fixed asset purchases: 1,213,417.20
- Accumulated depreciation: 115,511.91
= Net fixed assets end value: 9,097,905.29

- Fixed assets net End Value: 9,097,905.29
